[100.08612, "i", "cat > DEPLOYMENT_COMPLETE.txt << 'EOF'\n================================================================================\nDEPLOYMENT COMPLETE - Scheduler Timezone Bug Fix\n================================================================================\n\nISSUE: Meeting reminders were being sent at incorrect times, off by exactly\n       1 hour for meetings between 2am-3am Berlin time during DST transitions.\n\nROOT CAUSE: The convert_to_berlin() function in app.py was using\n            BERLIN_TZ.localize() on UTC timestamps, treating them as if they\n            were already in Berlin time instead of converting from UTC.\n\nFIX APPLIED: Changed timezone conversion to properly:\n             1. Localize the naive datetime as UTC\n             2. Convert the UTC-aware datetime to Berlin timezone\n\nFILES MODIFIED:\n  - /home/user/scheduler/app.py (FIXED)\n  - /home/user/scheduler/app.py.backup (original buggy version)\n\nVERIFICATION:\n  - Tested with verify_fix.py - all meetings now convert correctly\n  - The problematic \"Mainten"]
[100.086174, "i", "ance Window Prep\" meeting (2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC)\n    now correctly converts to 03:30 CEST instead of 01:30 CET\n  - All other meetings also fixed (were off by 1-2 hours)\n\nCRON JOB: Already installed and will use the fixed version\n  - Runs hourly: 0 * * * *\n  - Location: /home/user/scheduler/crontab\n  - Command: cd /home/user/scheduler && python3 app.py\n\nSTATUS: ✓ READY FOR PRODUCTION\n        The Monday 2:30am maintenance window reminder will now be sent\n        at the correct time.\n================================================================================\nEOF\n"]
